<p>I have been in Melbourne for about 11 months now and this afternoon, for the first time I visited the shopping centre of Boxhill. It is connected with the train line and surprisingly (or maybe not?) it is a place full of life, businesses, chattering and Asian faces. I almost felt like I was in China - a bit crowded, some people with bearable fashion taste (like I have any), and the rude Asian stares at me and Charles (to defend that I'll say Chinese people are nosy and they don't want to pretend they are not).</p>

